Date: 0/6/1860
Source: First Year in Canterbury Settlement
Author: BUTLER
Vol / Page: 6/74
Edition:
Quote: I had two cadets with me, and must explain that a cadet means a young fellow who has lately come out, and who wants to see a little of up-country life. He is neither paid nor pays. He receives his food and lodging gratis but works (or is supposed to work) in order to learn.
