Quote: The household consists ... of a cadet, as they are called - he is a clergyman's son learning sheep-farming under our auspices - and a boy who milks the cows ...
Notes:

Date: 0/0/1871
Source: Knocking About in NZ
Author: MONEY
Vol / Page: 6
Edition:
Quote: This military designation of cadet was applied to any young fellow who was attached to a sheep or cattle station in the same capacity as myself. He was neither `flesh, nor fowl, nor good red herring,' neither master nor man. In consideration of his `education,' he was permitted to reside and take his meals with the master, but was sent to work with the men - the essential difference between the latter and himself being that they were paid for their labour, ...
Notes:

Date: 3/2/1873
Source: Diary
Author: >G.M.WILSON
Vol / Page: 166
Edition:
Quote: There was a young fellow better looking than the shepherd ... He was a cadet, as they call the young fellows learning sheep farming here, but I am afraid he would not learn much at such a rough place.
Notes: 1873 Feb 3 G.M.Wilson Diary in 1973 Wierzbicka Wilson Family 166

